{"lemma":"دَخِيل","slug":"دَخِيل","root":"د.خ.ل","root_slug":"د-خ-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/د-خ-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12267"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%84"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"alien, extraneous (of foreign origin)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"exotic, non-native (non-native to the ecosystem)","examples":[{"text":"أنْوَاع دَخِيلَة","english":"non-native species"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"loan, foreign","examples":[{"text":"لَفْظ دَخِيل","english":"a loanword"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"intruder"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb دَخَلَ (daḵala, “to enter”)."},"ipa":["/da.xiːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12267","headword_ar":"دَخِيلٌ","root":"dxl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A guest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) Hence the saying of the vulgar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA daxiylu fulaAnK","text_ar":"اَنَا دَخِيلُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am the guest of such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"generally meaning I am under his protection]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxolulN","text_ar":"دُخْلُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An adventive abider"},{"kind":"text","text":"among a people.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN daxiylN bayona Alqawomi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ دَخِيلٌ بَيْنَ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is a person abiding among the people, not related to them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa daxiylN fiyhimo","text_ar":"هُوَ دَخِيلٌ فِيهِمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is a stranger to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has entered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who enters,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) applied also to a female. (TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalN","text_ar":"دَخَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is app. a quasi-pl. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxiylN","text_ar":"دَخِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense.] ―         -b4-  Hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A subject of discourse introduced by way of digression,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as having some relation to the class,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"category, of the proper subjects treated of, but not included therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A word that is adventitious, not indigenous, to the language of the Arabs; that is introduced into that language, and does not belong to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) There are many such words in the Jemharah of Ibn-Dureyd. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse that is introduced between two other horses in a race for a wager."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, O, TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHal~ilN","text_ar":"مُحَلِّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxiyliY~u","text_ar":"دَخِيلِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b7-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxolapN","text_ar":"دُخْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b8-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAxilN","text_ar":"دَاخِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  It is also said in the K to be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dixaAlN","text_ar":"دِخَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a sense explained above: see 6."}],"source_refs":["M","K"]}]}}